\section{Overview of the Asset Class and Companies}

The chosen asset class for this project is the \textbf{technology industry}. This sector encompasses companies specializing in software, hardware, semiconductors, and related services. The analysis will focus on the following companies:

\begin{itemize}
    \item Apple Inc. (AAPL)
    \item Adobe Inc. (ADBE)
    \item Advanced Micro Devices Inc. (AMD)
    \item eBay Inc. (EBAY)
    \item HP Inc. (HPQ)
    \item IBM Corporation (IBM)
    \item Juniper Networks Inc. (JNPR)
    \item Microsoft Corporation (MSFT)
    \item Oracle Corporation (ORCL)
    \item Qualcomm Inc. (QCOM)
\end{itemize}

% -----------------------
% Task 2
% -----------------------

\section{R Script for Analysis}

The R script used for the analysis is as follows:

\begin{lstlisting}[caption={R Script for Stock Price Analysis}, label={lst:rscriptexample}]
symbols <- c("AAPL", "ADBE", "AMD", "EBAY", "HPQ", "IBM", "JNPR", "MSFT", "ORCL", "QCOM")
getSymbols(symbols)
# AAPL Stock Price Plot
aapl_prices <- as.numeric(AAPL[, "AAPL.Close"])
aapl_dates <- index(AAPL)
plot(aapl_dates, aapl_prices, 
     type = "l",
     main = "AAPL Stock Price",
     xlab = "Date",
     ylab = "Price",
     col = "blue")
# Repeat similar analysis for other stocks...
\end{lstlisting}


