\section{Descriptive Statistics}

Using the R script, the log returns for AAPL were calculated, and the following statistics were derived:

\begin{itemize}
    \item Mean: 0.000951
    \item Variance: 0.000391
    \item Skewness: -0.3606
    \item Kurtosis: 6.6225
\end{itemize}

% -----------------------
% Conclusion
% -----------------------

\section{Conclusion}

The analysis of the technology industry asset class was conducted using an R script. Key outputs include stock price trends, histograms, and log return statistics. Future work will involve applying time series models to forecast returns and assess volatility.

